description: Real Time raw data quality monitoring for DUNE ND 2x2 detector

panels.description: Mean over 10s of data rates (expressed as packet count per second) by chip. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow / Red thresholds = 100 / 1k p/s
panels.title: Tile $tile . P$pacman: Data Rate by chip (10s Mean)

panels.description: Highest 100 Data Rates over the last 5m (expressed as # packets per second) by pixel for the chosen tile. Each value is a 10s Mean. Yellow / Red thresholds = 1 / 5 p/s
panels.title: T$tile . P$pacman: Top-100 Pixel Rates (5m Max)

panels.description: Histogram shows distribution of Pixel-level ADC 10s mean values over the global time window. The bucket size is 1. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. A value of 255 indicates the signal maxed out. Consistent 255 values (or consistent values below 5) may mean the threshold is set too high (or too low). Both problematic threshold cases could result in missing information.
panels.title: Tile $tile . P$pacman: ADC Mean Distribution - Pixel Level

panels.description: These are the highest 100 ADC 10s mean values in the chosen tile over the last 30s. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. A value of 255 indicates the ADC maxed out, which could mean we're missing information. This could require an expert to reset the threshold.  Yellow / Red thresholds = 250 / 254
panels.title: T$tile . P$pacman: Top 100 Pixel ADC Mean (30s Max)

panels.description: Configuration % = sum (config packet) / sum (total packet) for each 1s interval over entire system. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow threshold is 1%, Red threshold is 10%
panels.title: Tile $tile . P$pacman: Config Rate (1s Mean)

panels.description: Green bars are centered at Pixel-level Mean ADC value, the top/bottom of the bars are at Mean +/- RMS. All values are calculated over a 10s window.  Red thresholds are <5 or > 254. Yellow threshold is  > 250
panels.title: Tile $tile . P$pacman : ADC Value mean and rms (10s Mean) - Pixel Level

panels.description: FIFO > 1/2 (or Full) is the fraction of times the FIFO was more than half full (or Full) divided by the total number of observations over a 10s window. "Shared" FIFO is calculated at the chip level. This graph shows the mean chip level ratio for the entire system. This stacked bar chart shows the FIFO > 1/2 (but not completely full) as a blue bar. On top of the blue bar is FIFO full shown as a red bar. Yellow / Red Threshold = 0.1 / 0.2
panels.title: Tile $tile . P$pacman: Shared FIFO > 1/2 and Full (10s Max)

panels.description: FIFO > 1/2 (or Full) is the fraction of times the FIFO was more than half full (or Full) divided by the total number of observations over a 10s window. "Local" FIFO is calculated at the pixel level. This graph shows the mean pixel level ratio for the entire system. This stacked bar chart shows the FIFO > 1/2 (but not completely full) as a blue bar. On top of the blue bar is FIFO full shown as a red bar. Yellow / Red Threshold = 0.1 / 0.2
panels.title: Tile $tile . P$pacman: Local FIFO > 1/2 and Full (10s Max)

panels.description: Invalid parity indicates that bits flipped at some point in the packet's transmission from chip to pacman. Invalid Parity % = sum (invalid parity) / sum (total) for each 10s interval. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow threshold is 1%, Red threshold is 10%.
panels.title: Tile $tile . P$pacman: Mean Invalid % (10s Mean)

panels.description: Each tile has 4 Input-Output (IO) channels through which data is transmitted. For a given pacman each IO_channel is uniquely numbered from 1 to 32.
